# RepTrack iOS app: where to edit

**All edits for the RepTrack iOS (Swift/SwiftUI) app must go to the Xcode project the user actually builds and runs.**

- **Edit here (canonical):**  
  `/Users/mohamedansar/Documents/IOs projects/RepTrack/`  
  (iCloud Drive → Documents → IOs projects → RepTrack — the one opened in Xcode.)

- **Do not edit:**  
  The `RepTrack/` folder inside this workspace (`kmsmohamedansar.github.io/RepTrack`) for app code. That copy is not the one the user runs in the simulator.

When changing views, view models, models, or utilities for the iOS app, use full paths under:

`/Users/mohamedansar/Documents/IOs projects/RepTrack/RepTrack/`

Example: `.../IOs projects/RepTrack/RepTrack/Views/WorkoutDetailView.swift`, not `RepTrack/RepTrackApp/Views/...` in the repo.
